Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer position with Marriott International. I bring over three years of professional experience in backend services, RESTful APIs, and distributed systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect the technical depth and engineering rigor this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed, developed, and maintained backend services and RESTful APIs using Java, Spring Boot, and Webflux that translate natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1000+ endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across a distributed microservices surface. I built microservices solutions following OOP principles and design patterns, participating in system design discussions to accelerate platform API integration. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented a full observability and monitoring stack using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks to troubleshoot production issues, perform root cause analysis, and implement long-term fixes. I also architected a distributed systems orchestration layer using LangChain and LangGraph, enabling scalable backend execution with focus on security, scalability, and reliability throughout the development lifecycle. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to the backbone infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed, developed, and tested backend services and RESTful APIs using Java, Spring Boot, PostgreSQL, and SQL for an Identity & Access Management platform on AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications. I also built a cloud-native Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handles file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO through expiring signed URLs, writing clean, maintainable, well-documented code. I developed distributed systems workflows using AWS Step Functions and Lambda to handle long-running data import jobs, implementing automated testing and production support to ensure reliability. Throughout this role, I participated in code reviews, contributed to CI/CD automation improvements, and collaborated with product managers and QA engineers to deliver features end-to-end on time — all of which prepared me to contribute meaningfully to Marriott's core engineering responsibilities and deliver features from design through deployment and production support.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in algorithms, data structures, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture Marriott values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using CUDA and PyTorch on Pace University's HPC cluster, applying algorithms and data structures for efficient GPU-accelerated model training. I deployed models using vLLM for inference with Hugging Face, implementing CI/CD workflows for secure model serving with focus on scalability and reliability. Beyond building the systems myself, I led technical workshops on GPU programming and building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph for 50+ students, demonstrating strong communication skills and mentorship abilities. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the collaborative and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Marriott's engineering team.

I have always been passionate about putting people first and pursuing excellence — values that align deeply with Marriott International's mission to enhance lives through exceptional experiences and be the world's favorite travel company. I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering Marriott's goal of creating extraordinary experiences for guests while delivering high-quality, scalable backend systems that support the company's global hospitality operations. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

